(<i> buzzing</i> )

00:06.965 --> 00:08.258
(<i> rattling</i> )

00:08.341 --> 00:10.593
♪ ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE ♪

00:10.677 --> 00:13.263
<i>ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE.</i>

00:19.894 --> 00:22.605
♪ ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE ♪

00:22.689 --> 00:23.815
<i>ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE.</i>

00:23.898 --> 00:27.861
(<i> whistling and buzzing</i> )

00:28.278 --> 00:29.279
(<i> splat!</i> )

00:29.946 --> 00:30.947
(<i> screaming</i> )

00:31.030 --> 00:34.200
♪ ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE. ♪

00:34.284 --> 00:36.244
<i>ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE.</i>

00:37.620 --> 00:42.375
[Captioning sponsored by the
U.S. DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION]

00:42.459 --> 00:45.044
THAT WAS A HOOT!

00:58.767 --> 00:59.934
WOW!
TWO FRONT-ROW TICKETS

01:00.018 --> 01:04.147
TO WINK WELLINGTON
AND THE WING WALKERS.

01:04.230 --> 01:06.024
{\an1}THE CULTURAL EVENT
OF THE SEASON.

01:06.107 --> 01:09.152
I SEE YOU EVEN
HAD YOUR HAIR STYLED.

01:09.235 --> 01:11.738
IT TOOK TWO TUBES
OF STYLING GEL

01:11.821 --> 01:13.323
TO GET IT TO STAY.

01:15.492 --> 01:17.535
{\an1}Heff:
HEY, ROCKO, CAN I DRIVE?

01:17.619 --> 01:18.161
NO, HEFF.

01:18.244 --> 01:19.370
{\an1}(<i> whining</i> ):
PLEASE!

01:19.454 --> 01:21.331
NO.

01:21.414 --> 01:22.832
{\an1}YOU'RE STILL
NOT PEEVED

01:22.916 --> 01:25.376
{\an1}ABOUT THE POODLE
INCIDENT, ARE YOU?

01:25.460 --> 01:26.544
(<i> engine sputtering</i> )

01:26.628 --> 01:28.588
COME ON, BABY.

01:28.671 --> 01:32.842
(<i> engine choking and hiccuping</i> )

01:37.847 --> 01:38.556
(<i> backfiring</i> )

01:38.640 --> 01:39.724
THAT'S IT, HEFF.

01:39.808 --> 01:40.683
WE'LL HAVE TO PUSH.

01:40.767 --> 01:43.603
{\an1}I WISH I COULD,
ROCKO, BUT...

01:43.686 --> 01:47.148
{\an1}I PULLED MY HAMSTRING
LAST WEEK PLAYING JAI ALAI.

01:48.650 --> 01:53.404
{\an5}Heff:
FASTER, ROCKO,
IT'S ALMOST CURTAIN TIME.

01:54.447 --> 01:57.200
Rocko:
UH-OH, HEFF, IT'S SLIPPING.

01:57.283 --> 01:58.159
{\an3}WHAT?

01:58.243 --> 01:58.409
BRAKES, HEFF.

01:58.493 --> 02:00.328
{\an3}HUH?

02:00.411 --> 02:01.830
BRAKES!

02:01.913 --> 02:02.288
(<i> crash</i> )

02:04.290 --> 02:05.083
HONEST, ROCKO

02:05.166 --> 02:07.460
{\an1}I THOUGHT
YOU SAID "STEAKS."

02:07.544 --> 02:09.127
CAN YOU EVER
FORGIVE ME?

02:09.211 --> 02:10.128
OF COURSE, HEFF.

02:10.213 --> 02:11.881
IT WAS AN
HONEST MISTAKE.

02:11.965 --> 02:13.883
BUT I'M WORRIED ABOUT MY CAR.

02:13.967 --> 02:16.427
IT'S NEVER SOUNDED
THIS BAD BEFORE.

02:16.511 --> 02:17.637
(<i> banging</i> )

02:17.720 --> 02:20.473
WE'LL HAVE TO TAKE IT
TO THE SHOP TOMORROW.

02:28.857 --> 02:30.859
(<i> heavy breathing</i> )

02:30.942 --> 02:33.778
{\an1}YOU MUST BE
THE GRIM TOW TRUCK.

02:33.862 --> 02:35.655
{\an1}DOES THIS MEAN,
I'M, I'M....

02:35.738 --> 02:38.575
IT IS TIME
FOR YOU TO GO

02:38.658 --> 02:41.536
TO THAT BIG PARKING
LOT IN THE SKY.

02:43.329 --> 02:46.332
OH... ST. PETERBILT.

02:54.048 --> 02:57.093
{\an1}CAN I HELP YOU,
YOUNG FELLA?

02:57.176 --> 02:58.094
WHY, YES.

02:58.177 --> 02:59.888
I NEED MY CAR FIXED.

03:00.680 --> 03:02.098
THAT CAR?

03:02.181 --> 03:04.475
(<i> laughing</i> )

03:05.351 --> 03:07.770
OH, I'M SORRY,
YOU'RE SERIOUS.

03:07.854 --> 03:08.938
YES, I'M SERIOUS.

03:09.022 --> 03:11.274
I'D LIKE TO GET
MY CAR FIXED.

03:13.568 --> 03:17.280
SIR... THAT CHEAP,
LITTLE RATTLETRAP IS NOT A CAR.

03:17.989 --> 03:20.825
<i>THIS</i> IS A CAR.

03:20.909 --> 03:22.744
THIS IS A CAR.

03:22.827 --> 03:26.122
WHAT YOU GOT THERE
IS A LITTLE TRICYCLE

03:26.205 --> 03:26.915
WITH AN EXTRA WHEEL.

03:26.998 --> 03:33.296
(<i> garage guys laughing</i> )

03:34.213 --> 03:36.799
YOU SEE...
ME AND MY BUDDIES RACE

03:36.883 --> 03:40.303
IN THE O-TOWN RALLY
EVERY YEAR.

03:40.386 --> 03:41.262
AND, WELL...

03:41.346 --> 03:44.933
WE EAT CARS LIKE YOURS
FOR BREAKFAST.

03:45.016 --> 03:47.727
WHY, THIS OLD WRECK
AIN'T WORTH FIXING.

03:47.810 --> 03:49.896
BE BETTER OFF
SELLING IT FOR SCRAP.

03:49.979 --> 03:51.064
SCRAP!

03:51.147 --> 03:52.482
THIS IS A GREAT CAR.

03:52.565 --> 03:54.025
IT'S THE CAR
I LEARNED TO DRIVE IN.

03:54.108 --> 03:57.278
THE CAR THAT BROUGHT
ME TO O-TOWN.

03:57.362 --> 03:58.696
{\an1}I'VE HAD SOME WONDERFUL
TIMES IN THIS CAR.

03:58.780 --> 04:00.657
HEAR THAT, BOYS?

04:00.740 --> 04:02.784
{\an1}THE PLATYPUS
IS ALL SENTIMENTAL

04:02.867 --> 04:04.577
{\an1}ABOUT HIS
LITTLE RED WAGON.

04:04.661 --> 04:06.996
(<i> laughing</i> )

04:07.080 --> 04:10.249
{\an1}WELL, LET ME TELL YOU
SOMETHING, MISTER.

04:10.333 --> 04:11.334
I'M GOING
TO FIX MY CAR

04:11.417 --> 04:15.964
{\an1}AND WHAT'S MORE, I'M GOING
TO WIN THAT RACE.

04:16.047 --> 04:17.173
RIGHT ON!

04:17.257 --> 04:17.757
YOU TELL 'EM, ROCKO.

04:17.839 --> 04:21.010
HEFFER, PUSH ME HOME.

04:21.094 --> 04:23.513
I TOLD YOU, ROCK,
I GOT THIS HAMSTRING.

04:23.596 --> 04:26.599
OH, FOR CRYING OUT LOUD!

04:26.683 --> 04:28.059
(<i> guys guffawing</i> )

04:32.855 --> 04:34.274
Rocko:
ALL RIGHT, HEFF.

04:34.357 --> 04:36.567
LET'S TAKE STOCK
OF OUR SITUATION.

04:36.651 --> 04:38.069
I GOT, UH...

04:38.152 --> 04:42.699
{\an1}A TOOLBOX
AND, UH, REPAIR MANUAL.

04:42.782 --> 04:44.283
WE'LL CHECK OUT
THE TOOLS FIRST.

04:46.494 --> 04:47.328
{\an1}GEE, ROCKO

04:47.412 --> 04:49.706
{\an1}IT'S SORT OF LIMITED,
SELECTION-WISE.

04:49.789 --> 04:51.708
{\an1}WELL,
WE'LL IMPROVISE.

04:51.791 --> 04:53.501
LET'S CONSULT
THE REPAIR MANUAL.

04:58.381 --> 05:00.550
{\an1}OKAY, HEFF, YOU READ
WHILE I WORK.

05:00.633 --> 05:01.926
OKEY-DOKEY.

05:02.010 --> 05:06.055
{\an5}(<i> in Slavic accent</i> ):
"FIRST, TO BE PUTTING CAR
IN NEUTRAL."

05:06.139 --> 05:08.141
{\an1}DON'T AFFECT
THE SILLY ACCENT.

05:08.224 --> 05:09.642
BUT THAT'S
HOW IT'S WRITTEN.

05:09.726 --> 05:11.019
{\an1}WHERE WAS
THIS CAR MADE?

05:11.102 --> 05:14.313
SLOO-BAVIA.

05:17.483 --> 05:20.778
"FIRST REMOVE OUTER
HOUSING PLATE SCREWS."

05:20.862 --> 05:22.697
(<i> clanking</i> )

05:22.780 --> 05:24.073
"BUT NOT
BEFORE TURNING

05:24.157 --> 05:24.866
"THE UPPER
RETENTION BOLT

05:24.949 --> 05:27.410
ONE HALF-TURN
CLOCKWISE."

05:28.995 --> 05:33.583
"THIS COULD BE
A VERY COSTLY MISTAKE."

05:36.919 --> 05:39.881
(<i> sniffing</i> )

05:41.299 --> 05:44.218
HEFFER, WHERE'S MY SCREWDRIVER?

05:44.302 --> 05:46.929
AND ALL THE OTHER PARTS
I PUT HERE.

05:47.013 --> 05:49.098
I DON'T KNOW,
BUT THEY'LL TURN UP.

05:49.182 --> 05:52.435
(<i> burping</i> )

05:53.394 --> 05:54.228
IT'S USELESS.

05:54.312 --> 05:56.522
WE'LL NEVER GET
THE CAR FIXED.

05:56.606 --> 05:57.482
HI, GUYS.

05:57.565 --> 05:58.524
WHAT YOU DOING?

05:58.608 --> 05:59.609
{\an1}WE WERE TRYING TO FIX
MY CAR, ACTUALLY.

05:59.692 --> 06:00.777
OH, REALLY?

06:00.860 --> 06:03.279
LET ME HAVE A LOOK.

06:03.362 --> 06:04.989
YOU KNOW ABOUT CARS?

06:05.073 --> 06:05.948
OH, YEAH.

06:06.032 --> 06:09.035
I'M A GRADUATE
OF THE ADEQUACY-BY-MAIL

06:09.118 --> 06:11.662
MECHANIC CORRESPONDENCE SCHOOL.

06:11.746 --> 06:13.164
OUR MOTTO IS

06:13.247 --> 06:17.335
{\an1}"IF THE JOB'S WORTH DOING
IT'S WORTH DOING ADEQUATELY."

06:17.418 --> 06:20.088
{\an1}DO YOU THINK
YOU CAN MAKE IT BETTER?

06:20.171 --> 06:21.172
{\an3}BETTER?

06:21.255 --> 06:23.966
{\an1}WE CAN MAKE IT
BETTER THAN IT WAS...

06:24.050 --> 06:27.804
BETTER, STRONGER, FASTER.

06:27.887 --> 06:29.639
WE CAN BRING IT BACK.

06:29.722 --> 06:31.766
WE CAN BRING IT BACK!

06:31.849 --> 06:35.478
RE-ANIMATE
THE LIFELESS SCRAP METAL

06:35.561 --> 06:36.395
AND RETURN TO IT

06:36.479 --> 06:41.442
THAT SPARK
THAT IS THE BREATH OF LIFE

06:41.526 --> 06:42.902
ITSELF!

06:42.985 --> 06:45.905
(<i> laughing crazily</i> )

06:45.988 --> 06:48.825
(<i> thundering</i> )

06:50.409 --> 06:53.329
WELL, IT WORKED
IN THE MOVIE.

06:53.412 --> 06:55.540
{\an1}MAYBE WE SHOULD
TRY SOMETHING ELSE.

06:57.708 --> 07:00.002
FORCEPS!

07:00.086 --> 07:02.296
(<i> metal clanking</i> )

07:02.380 --> 07:03.631
SCREWDRIVER.

07:06.134 --> 07:07.426
SUCTION.

07:07.885 --> 07:09.637
PIPE WRENCH.

07:11.097 --> 07:13.015
(<i> metallic ringing</i> )

07:13.099 --> 07:14.809
SILLY HEADDRESS.

07:14.892 --> 07:16.853
LIVE CHICKEN.

07:16.936 --> 07:18.688
(<i> squawk</i> )

07:18.771 --> 07:22.692
BOOM SCHWATI OOSH!

07:22.775 --> 07:24.235
IS THAT NECESSARY?

07:24.318 --> 07:24.569
IT COULDN'T HURT.

07:25.945 --> 07:28.197
NOW, IF I'M RIGHT

07:28.281 --> 07:31.033
{\an1}I CAN JUST RE-ATTACH
THE BATTERY CABLES

07:31.117 --> 07:33.578
AND WE'LL BE DONE.

07:33.661 --> 07:35.079
OKAY, LET'S SEE.

07:35.163 --> 07:38.875
{\an1}IT'S BLACK TO POSITIVE,
RED TO NEGATIVE...

07:38.958 --> 07:40.710
(<i> electrical static</i> )

07:40.793 --> 07:42.503
NO, THAT'S NOT RIGHT.

07:43.796 --> 07:45.715
THAT'S IT.
I GIVE UP.

07:45.798 --> 07:46.257
IT'S HOPELESS.

07:46.340 --> 07:48.968
I'VE TRIED EVERYTHING

07:49.051 --> 07:51.345
EVERYTHING
I CAN THINK OF.

07:51.429 --> 07:52.513
IT'S USELESS.

07:52.597 --> 07:54.974
A LOST CAUSE,
BEYOND HOPE.

07:55.057 --> 07:57.310
{\an5}AHEM!

07:55.057 --> 07:57.310
OVERDONE,
KAPUT!

07:57.393 --> 08:00.938
FILBURT, I DIDN'T GRADUATE
FROM A SCHOOL OR ANYTHING

08:01.022 --> 08:01.898
BUT I JUST NOTICED SOMETHING.

08:01.981 --> 08:03.858
WHAT IS IT?

08:03.941 --> 08:05.443
WELL,
THERE'S A SWITCH

08:05.526 --> 08:06.903
HERE ON THE ENGINE.

08:06.986 --> 08:08.487
PERHAPS IF WE SWITCHED IT

08:08.571 --> 08:10.072
FROM BROKEN TO FIXED...

08:10.156 --> 08:12.408
YOU KNOW SOMETHING?

08:12.491 --> 08:16.662
THAT'S JUST
CRAZY ENOUGH TO WORK.

08:16.746 --> 08:18.831
HELLO, SON.

08:18.915 --> 08:22.627
{\an1}LET ME OPEN
THAT PEARLY GARAGE DOOR.

08:27.548 --> 08:29.175
HEFFER, YOU GET
IN THE CAR

08:29.258 --> 08:32.929
AND GET READY
TO START IT UP.

08:33.011 --> 08:35.472
ROCKO,
FLIP THAT SWITCH.

08:37.475 --> 08:38.476
AH, WAIT.

08:38.558 --> 08:43.272
I'M AFRAID WE MAY HAVE BEEN
A LITTLE PREMATURE.

08:46.817 --> 08:49.528
ALL RIGHT, HEFFER, START IT UP.

08:53.366 --> 08:55.451
(<i> engine sputtering</i> )

08:55.534 --> 08:56.911
IT'S ALIVE.

08:56.994 --> 09:01.165
IT'S ALIVE!

09:02.208 --> 09:04.585
GUYS, I THINK
I JUST KNOCKED IN THE...

09:04.669 --> 09:06.504
(<i> Heffer screaming</i> )

09:08.506 --> 09:09.632
{\an1}OH, DEAR.

09:09.715 --> 09:13.469
{\an1}I HAVEN'T RECONNECTED
THE ACCELERATOR OR TURNSPRINGS

09:13.552 --> 09:16.639
THE TRANSMISSION CABLE
OR THE BRAKE PADS YET.

09:16.722 --> 09:17.974
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

09:18.057 --> 09:20.059
{\an1}HE'S GOING TO
CAREEN FULL TILT

09:20.142 --> 09:21.727
{\an1}THROUGH THE TOWN
IN REVERSE

09:21.811 --> 09:23.729
TILL HE EITHER
HITS A BUILDING

09:23.813 --> 09:26.232
{\an1}OR THE ENGINE OVERHEATS
AND EXPLODES.

09:26.315 --> 09:27.149
EXPLODES!

09:27.233 --> 09:29.443
WHAT'S GOING
TO HAPPEN TO HEFFER THEN?

09:29.527 --> 09:30.987
OH, DEAR.

09:31.070 --> 09:33.364
WE GOT TO SAVE HIM.

09:33.447 --> 09:36.117
{\an1}COME ON, FILBURT,
WE CAN STILL CATCH HIM.

09:36.200 --> 09:38.160
OKAY, BUT I'VE
GOT TO DRIVE.

09:38.244 --> 09:39.161
I'M NOT INSURED FOR YOU.

09:39.245 --> 09:44.000
(<i> Heffer screaming</i> )

09:44.083 --> 09:46.502
{\an1}MAKE SURE YOUR
HELMET FITS SNUGLY

09:46.586 --> 09:50.923
{\an1}BUT NOT SO TIGHT AS TO CUT OFF
CIRCULATION TO THE BRAIN.

09:52.300 --> 09:54.051
TIRES, CHECK.

09:54.135 --> 09:57.221
GAS GAUGE, CHECK.

09:57.305 --> 09:58.556
IS THIS NECESSARY?

09:58.639 --> 10:00.641
THERE'S ALWAYS TIME
FOR SAFETY, ROCKO.

10:00.725 --> 10:03.728
(<i> tires squealing,</i>
<i>horn blaring</i> )

10:03.811 --> 10:06.105
(<i> Heffer screaming</i> )

10:07.815 --> 10:08.941
AIRBAGS?

10:09.025 --> 10:10.943
CHECK.

10:11.944 --> 10:14.030
(<i> horn blaring</i> )

10:15.072 --> 10:17.325
CHECK RIGHT, CHECK LEFT.

10:17.408 --> 10:18.868
SIGNAL, AND...

10:18.951 --> 10:20.453
PULL INTO TRAFFIC.

10:24.373 --> 10:26.834
(<i> train whistle blowing</i> )

10:26.917 --> 10:29.128
ROCKO, ROCKO, HELP!

10:29.211 --> 10:29.754
(<i> crossing bell ringing</i> )

10:35.801 --> 10:37.386
THANKS, ROCK!

10:44.602 --> 10:45.895
HOP ON, ROCK.

10:45.978 --> 10:48.230
WE CAN STILL CATCH HIM.

10:48.314 --> 10:49.190
I KNOW A SHORTCUT.

10:49.273 --> 10:52.401
(<i> screaming</i> )

11:06.791 --> 11:08.417
HEY, I'M IN THE RACE!

11:08.501 --> 11:12.630
I'LL SHOW THESE GUYS
WHAT ROCKO'S CAR'S MADE OF.

11:13.130 --> 11:13.714
YA-HOO!

11:13.798 --> 11:14.673
I'LL TEACH YOU TO MAKE FUN

11:14.757 --> 11:18.594
OF CHEAP, LITTLE,
POORLY MADE ECONOMY CARS.

11:18.677 --> 11:21.472
Rocko:
DO YOU KNOW WHERE YOU'RE GOING?

11:21.555 --> 11:23.224
IT LOOKS LIKE WE'RE LOST.

11:23.307 --> 11:24.308
Heffer:
YA-HOO!

11:24.392 --> 11:28.562
OH, YE OF LITTLE FAITH.

11:31.315 --> 11:33.734
{\an1}HEFF,
JUMP OVER HERE.

11:33.818 --> 11:35.444
I CAN'T LEAVE NOW, ROCK.

11:35.528 --> 11:38.989
{\an5}I'M ABOUT TO
WIN THE RACE
WITH YOUR CAR.

11:39.073 --> 11:40.282
ISN'T IT GREAT?

11:40.366 --> 11:43.452
BUT FILBURT SAYS THE ENGINE
COULD EXPLODE AT ANY MINUTE.

11:43.536 --> 11:47.456
YOU KNOW, WINNING
IS HIGHLY OVERRATED.

11:50.751 --> 11:52.420
HEFFER, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

11:52.503 --> 11:53.504
THAT'S DANGEROUS.

11:53.587 --> 11:54.463
HERE, PUT
THIS HELMET ON.

11:54.547 --> 11:57.633
THERE'S ALWAYS TIME
FOR SAFETY.

11:57.716 --> 12:01.303
{\an1}AT LEAST WE GOT YOU OFF
BEFORE THE ENGINE EXPLODES.

12:01.387 --> 12:02.304
WHICH SHOULD BE ANY MINUTE NOW.

12:02.388 --> 12:04.432
(<i> cheering</i> )

12:04.515 --> 12:07.309
(<i> sputtering, backfiring</i> )

12:08.519 --> 12:12.440
OR MAYBE IT'LL JUST
RUN OUT OF GAS.

12:13.941 --> 12:16.318
CHEER UP, ROCKO,
WE CAME IN SECOND.

12:16.402 --> 12:17.862
{\an1}YOUR CAR
CAME IN FIRST.

12:17.945 --> 12:20.990
{\an1}SO IT GETS A TROPHY
AND A FREE TANK OF GAS.

12:21.073 --> 12:23.367
A TANK OF GAS?

12:23.451 --> 12:25.661
{\an3}OH, BOY.

12:36.088 --> 12:38.215
OH, WELL...

12:38.299 --> 12:40.176
HERE WE GO AGAIN.

12:40.885 --> 12:44.096
BOOM SCHWATI OOSH!

12:57.526 --> 13:02.072
(<i> bluesy harmonica tune</i>
<i>playing</i> )

13:05.534 --> 13:07.161
I GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

13:07.244 --> 13:09.205
{\an1}I'M A FLY.

13:09.288 --> 13:12.958
I GOT TO BE FREE!

13:14.251 --> 13:16.545
HUH, GOTCHA.

13:16.629 --> 13:19.089
Fly:
I GUESS THIS IS IT, BOYS.

13:19.173 --> 13:21.175
FLECKO!

13:22.468 --> 13:26.388
{\an1}HEY, YOU GET TO JOIN ME
FOR A LITTLE MIDNIGHT SNACK.

13:32.311 --> 13:33.020
HEY!

13:33.103 --> 13:35.606
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING?

13:35.689 --> 13:36.649
{\an3}GET OFF!

13:36.732 --> 13:39.235
OOH, THINK
YOU'RE PRETTY SMART?

13:39.318 --> 13:41.820
WELL, NOT AS SMART
AS ED BIGHEAD.

13:41.904 --> 13:44.365
I'LL SAVE <i> YOU</i> FOR LATER.

13:44.448 --> 13:47.618
(<i> chuckling</i> )

13:51.330 --> 13:53.707
LET'S EAT.

13:53.791 --> 13:55.918
(<i> bugs shouting</i> )

13:56.001 --> 13:57.795
AH, GEE.

13:57.878 --> 13:59.296
MY BUDDIES.

13:59.380 --> 14:00.881
(<i> bugs shrieking</i> )

14:02.091 --> 14:02.383
MMM.

14:02.466 --> 14:04.426
OOH, MMM.

14:04.510 --> 14:05.970
(<i> gulps</i> )

14:06.053 --> 14:06.595
(<i> chuckling</i> )

14:06.679 --> 14:09.557
NOW, TO WASH THEM DOWN...

14:13.102 --> 14:14.979
(<i> gulping</i> )

14:20.859 --> 14:22.278
(<i> screaming</i> )

14:22.361 --> 14:24.321
OW!

14:25.823 --> 14:27.241
WHY, YOU...!

14:35.207 --> 14:37.167
(<i> sniffing</i> )

14:40.713 --> 14:43.299
(<i> disposal whirring,</i>
<i>Ed screaming</i> )

14:48.554 --> 14:52.266
(<i> buzzing</i> )

14:54.143 --> 14:55.102
(<i> buzzing</i> )

15:00.357 --> 15:01.483
Flecko:
MMM, NOT BAD.

15:01.567 --> 15:02.985
(<i> toilet flushes</i> )

15:03.068 --> 15:04.528
OH, NO!

15:04.612 --> 15:06.697
(<i> yawning</i> )

15:11.744 --> 15:13.746
Rocko:
OOPS.

15:13.829 --> 15:14.371
OH, SORRY.

15:14.455 --> 15:17.583
{\an1}AFTER YOU.

15:17.666 --> 15:20.002
THERE, NO HARM DONE.

15:21.211 --> 15:25.507
WOW, I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

15:26.759 --> 15:28.218
(<i> bluesy harmonica</i> )

15:28.302 --> 15:29.595
TOO BAD ABOUT FLECKO.

15:29.678 --> 15:31.597
I GUESS WE'RE NEXT
ON THE MENU.

15:31.680 --> 15:33.140
{\an1}Flecko:
GUESS AGAIN.

15:33.223 --> 15:35.017
STAND BACK, BOYS.

15:35.100 --> 15:36.226
FLECKO!

15:41.565 --> 15:43.525
FOLLOW ME TO FREEDOM.

15:43.609 --> 15:46.320
(<i> bugs cheering</i> )

15:48.447 --> 15:49.740
(<i> alarm clock rings</i> )

15:49.823 --> 15:53.285
(<i> Rocko yawning</i> )

15:53.369 --> 15:54.703
GOOD MORNING, MR. BUG.

15:54.787 --> 15:56.872
GOOD MORNING, ROCKO.

15:56.955 --> 15:59.208
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

15:59.291 --> 16:02.211
YES, IT CERTAINLY IS.

16:03.462 --> 16:05.297
(<i> music from</i> Psycho <i> plays</i> )

16:05.381 --> 16:08.759
(<i> rock and roll music playing</i> )

16:19.311 --> 16:20.354
(<i> buzzing</i> )

16:20.437 --> 16:21.647
YOU SURE FOUND US

16:21.730 --> 16:24.400
{\an1}A GREAT PLACE
TO LIVE, FLECKO.

16:24.483 --> 16:25.567
YEAH.

16:25.651 --> 16:27.903
THIS GUY WOULDN'T
HURT A FLY.

16:27.986 --> 16:29.697
UM, EXCUSE ME.

16:29.780 --> 16:32.741
{\an1}I REALIZE THAT YOU ALL
JUST NEED A PLACE TO STAY

16:32.825 --> 16:34.827
BUT I HAVE TO ASK YOU TO LEAVE.

16:34.910 --> 16:37.079
(<i> bugs laughing</i> )

16:39.373 --> 16:41.417
PLEASE?

16:41.500 --> 16:43.961
(<i> bugs continue laughing</i> )

16:44.753 --> 16:47.005
AH, GO ON WITH YOU.

16:47.089 --> 16:50.384
IF THAT'S THE WAY
THAT YOU WANT IT, THEN I'LL...

16:50.467 --> 16:52.469
I'LL SIC MY FEROCIOUS DOG
ON YOU.

16:52.553 --> 16:55.472
(<i> whimpering</i> )

16:57.516 --> 17:00.060
SIC 'EM, SPUNKY.

17:01.854 --> 17:03.480
(<i> yapping</i> )

17:03.564 --> 17:06.983
(<i> roaring</i> )

17:07.067 --> 17:08.152
(<i> yelping</i> )

17:09.944 --> 17:12.448
(<i> bugs laughing</i> )

17:12.531 --> 17:15.451
UM, YOU DON'T WANT TO LIVE HERE.

17:15.534 --> 17:18.662
WHY DON'T YOU MOVE
SOMEPLACE NICE?

17:18.746 --> 17:22.624
{\an5}Bev:
ED, YOUR BREAKFAST'S
ON THE TABLE.

17:22.708 --> 17:28.630
MMM, TOAST, JUICE
AND A FRESH BOWL OF BUGS.

17:28.714 --> 17:30.966
TA-TA, TA-TA-TA.

17:31.049 --> 17:32.092
MMM.

17:32.176 --> 17:34.261
WHAT THE...?

17:34.344 --> 17:37.556
BEV, MY BUGS ARE GONE!

17:39.808 --> 17:42.060
(<i> buzzing</i> )

17:42.144 --> 17:44.480
HELLO, I NEED AN EXTERMINATOR.

17:44.563 --> 17:45.647
WELL, I'M YOUR BOY.

17:45.731 --> 17:48.525
{\an1}THAT'S THE ONLY REASON
I WAS PUT ON THIS OLD EARTH

17:48.609 --> 17:50.986
WAS TO KILL BUGS.

17:51.069 --> 17:53.489
I LOVE TO CHOP THEM
AND SQUISH THEM

17:53.572 --> 17:55.157
AND STOMP THEM AND GAS THEM.

17:55.240 --> 17:58.035
{\an1}EW! I DON'T WANT TO HURT
THE LITTLE FELLAS.

17:58.118 --> 17:59.912
I JUST WANT THEM OUT OF HERE.

17:59.995 --> 18:01.789
(<i> doorbell</i>
<i>chimes</i> )

18:02.831 --> 18:05.626
ROCKO, COULD I BORROW
A CUP OF BUGS?

18:05.709 --> 18:07.711
UH... UH, BUTTER?

18:07.795 --> 18:10.172
SURE, IF YOU CAN FIND IT.

18:12.966 --> 18:14.510
OH, YOU SEEM TO HAVE

18:14.593 --> 18:17.012
{\an1}A BIT OF A BUG PROBLEM,
NEIGHBOR.

18:17.096 --> 18:19.389
{\an1}I CAN GET RID OF THEM
FOR YOU.

18:19.473 --> 18:20.641
YOU CAN?

18:20.724 --> 18:22.726
OH, YES.

18:22.810 --> 18:24.394
YOU WON'T HURT THEM, WILL YOU?

18:24.478 --> 18:25.395
HMM?

18:25.479 --> 18:27.815
OH, NO, NO.

18:27.898 --> 18:28.857
I'LL, UH...

18:28.941 --> 18:31.193
OH, I'LL SEND THEM TO CAMP, HUH?

18:31.276 --> 18:34.696
{\an1}YES, I'LL SEND
THE BUGS TO CAMP.

18:34.780 --> 18:37.032
HOW VERY THOUGHTFUL.

18:37.115 --> 18:39.034
GO RIGHT AHEAD.

18:41.370 --> 18:43.705
All (<i> screaming</i> ):
ED BIGHEAD!

18:43.789 --> 18:46.375
ED BIGHEAD!

18:46.458 --> 18:47.918
All (<i> screaming</i> ):
ED?!

18:48.001 --> 18:51.255
(<i> screaming</i> )

18:51.338 --> 18:56.051
COME OUT, COME OUT,
WHEREVER YOU ARE.

18:56.844 --> 18:59.638
{\an1}(<i> vacuum cleaner</i>
<i>whirring</i> )

19:00.305 --> 19:01.348
(<i> screaming</i> )

19:12.818 --> 19:16.029
(<i> bugs screaming</i> )

19:18.282 --> 19:20.409
THANK YOU AGAIN, MR. BIGHEAD.

19:20.492 --> 19:21.827
{\an1}OH, YEAH, YEAH,
SURE.

19:21.910 --> 19:24.997
BYE, BUGS, HAVE FUN AT CAMP.

19:25.080 --> 19:27.082
WHAT A NICE MAN.

19:29.710 --> 19:33.255
{\an1}SOMETHING'S GOT TO BE DONE
ABOUT THAT ED BIGHEAD.

19:33.338 --> 19:36.675
AND I'M JUST THE GUY TO DO IT.

19:36.758 --> 19:38.010
HEY, WHAT THE...?

19:38.093 --> 19:39.636
THERE, THERE, NO WORRIES.

19:39.720 --> 19:42.389
{\an1}I'LL SEE THAT YOU GET TO
THE CAMP WITH YOUR FRIENDS.

19:46.768 --> 19:49.646
OH, HELLO,
ROCKO.

19:49.730 --> 19:52.691
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR THE BUGS, DEAR.

19:52.774 --> 19:54.776
YOU HAVE MADE ED VERY HAPPY.

19:54.860 --> 19:56.278
{\an3}COME IN,
DARLING.

19:56.361 --> 19:59.197
{\an5}ED'S JUST
PREPARING
THEM NOW.

19:59.281 --> 20:00.282
PREPARING?

20:02.701 --> 20:04.119
MM-MMM.

20:04.202 --> 20:06.997
ROACH SOUFFLE AND BUG <i> AU GRATIN.</i>

20:07.080 --> 20:10.792
{\an1}DOESN'T THAT JUST MAKE
YOUR LITTLE MOUTHS WATER?

20:10.876 --> 20:12.669
(<i> muffled screaming</i> )

20:12.753 --> 20:14.504
{\an1}Rocko:
OH, MR. BIGHEAD?

20:14.588 --> 20:15.714
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

20:15.797 --> 20:17.466
I BROUGHT ONE MORE FOR YOU
TO TAKE TO CAMP.

20:17.549 --> 20:18.467
OH... RIGHT!

20:18.550 --> 20:20.302
CAMP, CAMP.

20:20.385 --> 20:22.095
(<i> yells</i> ):
NOW, GET OUT!

20:22.179 --> 20:23.555
AH...

20:23.639 --> 20:26.016
NOW, WHERE WAS I?

20:26.099 --> 20:28.268
WELL, GOOD-BYE, MR. FLY.

20:28.352 --> 20:29.394
HAVE A GOOD TIME...

20:31.188 --> 20:35.233
"HE'S... GOING...
TO... EAT... US...

20:35.317 --> 20:37.736
YOU IDIOT!"

20:37.819 --> 20:40.113
EAT YOU?!

20:40.197 --> 20:43.617
{\an1}<i>"TOAD DIGEST</i>
<i>BUG RECIPES"?!</i>

20:59.675 --> 21:01.134
OKAY, FLY.

21:01.218 --> 21:03.720
NOW YOU'RE GOING TO GET IT.

21:05.931 --> 21:07.975
{\an1}Flecko:
HEY, FATHEAD.

21:08.058 --> 21:09.309
{\an1}DOWN HERE.

21:13.897 --> 21:16.733
(<i> sizzling</i> )

21:22.948 --> 21:24.574
OUT OF THE WAY, WALLABY!

21:24.658 --> 21:25.909
ALL RIGHT, FLY.

21:25.993 --> 21:28.495
I'M GOING TO BREAK
YOUR LITTLE HEAD.

21:28.578 --> 21:30.914
I'LL MURDELIZE YOU.

21:30.998 --> 21:31.415
WHAT THE...?

21:35.377 --> 21:36.253
{\an3}HIYA.

21:36.336 --> 21:37.587
(<i> gasping</i> )

21:42.968 --> 21:44.886
(<i> piano crashes</i> )

21:50.600 --> 21:52.561
OH... MR. BIGHEAD

21:52.644 --> 21:54.563
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

21:54.646 --> 21:58.108
AH... WHY, YES.

21:58.191 --> 21:59.568
FINE.

21:59.651 --> 22:01.445
WELL, GOOD.

22:01.528 --> 22:02.612
SAY, MR. BIGHEAD

22:02.696 --> 22:04.573
{\an1}I THINK I'LL TAKE
THE BUGS BACK HOME, OKAY?

22:04.656 --> 22:07.034
BUGS?

22:07.117 --> 22:08.035
WHAT ARE BUGS?

22:08.118 --> 22:09.494
GOOD NIGHT,
MR. BIGHEAD.

22:09.578 --> 22:12.122
BUGS?

22:12.205 --> 22:14.583
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT BUGS.

22:14.666 --> 22:16.918
(<i> muffled screaming</i> )

22:17.002 --> 22:18.170
THERE, THERE.

22:18.253 --> 22:20.130
YOU'LL BE FREE SOON.

22:23.925 --> 22:28.930
{\an1}WHY, ROCKO, HOW GOOD OF YOU
TO BRING IN THE BUGS.

22:30.474 --> 22:32.225
ED, HURRY UP!

22:32.309 --> 22:35.395
OH, MR. BIGHEAD IS, UH... UM...

22:35.479 --> 22:38.023
TAKING A LITTLE NAP
BEFORE DINNER.

22:38.106 --> 22:39.775
OH, THAT FIGURES.

22:39.858 --> 22:42.360
WE'LL JUST EAT THESE
LATER, THEN.

22:42.444 --> 22:43.820
UH, MRS. BIGHEAD?

22:43.904 --> 22:45.947
WHAT IS IT, DEAR?

22:46.031 --> 22:47.115
UM...

22:47.199 --> 22:48.533
(<i> gulps</i> )

22:48.617 --> 22:49.618
I SURE COULD GO

22:49.701 --> 22:52.662
FOR SOME OF THOSE
DELICIOUS BUGS RIGHT NOW.

22:52.746 --> 22:55.582
{\an1}WHY DIDN'T YOU
SAY SO?

22:55.665 --> 22:58.835
HERE, HELP YOURSELF.

23:03.256 --> 23:05.008
All (<i> cheering</i> ):
BUGS!

23:05.092 --> 23:07.928
I'D LIKE SOME MORE, PLEASE.

23:08.011 --> 23:11.139
(<i> buzzing</i> )

23:13.266 --> 23:14.518
MORE, PLEASE.

23:17.020 --> 23:17.479
(<i> muffled</i> ):
MORE, PLEASE.

23:21.608 --> 23:23.819
SOME MORE,
PLEASE.

23:23.902 --> 23:26.780
SORRY, FRESH OUT.

23:26.863 --> 23:28.907
I HATE TO EAT AND RUN

23:28.990 --> 23:31.743
BUT I REALLY MUST BE GOING.

23:35.247 --> 23:37.958
WHAT A PIG.

23:43.880 --> 23:47.217
(<i> Rocko retching</i> )

23:47.884 --> 23:50.512
(<i> gargling</i> )

23:52.514 --> 23:54.516
{\an1}(<i> Rocko</i>
<i>spitting</i> )

23:54.599 --> 23:56.309
{\an1}HEY, IT WAS NO PICNIC
FOR US EITHER.

23:56.393 --> 23:59.688
{\an4}Flecko:
WELL, PAL,
I GUESS THIS IS IT.

23:59.771 --> 24:01.648
FOR YOUR VALOR
AND RESCUING US

24:01.731 --> 24:03.775
{\an1}FROM A VERY
UNPLEASANT EXPERIENCE

24:03.859 --> 24:06.069
{\an1}WE HAVE DECIDED
TO TAKE OUR LEAVE.

24:06.153 --> 24:09.156
THAT ISLAND CRUISE YOU MENTIONED
SOUNDS GOOD TO US.

24:09.239 --> 24:11.950
WE COULD USE A VACATION.

24:13.785 --> 24:15.996
People (<i> shouting</i> ):
BUGS, BUGS, BUGS...

24:16.079 --> 24:19.875
Man:
I HATE BUGS...!

